This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=2945

This is a complete plugin with lots of tools to make editing of TeX/LaTeX file more friendly. Its main features include: background compilation, forward and inverse search for both dvi and pdf (okular), extended completion, AMSRef equry for bibliography references, font preview, support for projects with multiple tex files, and much more. For a detailed list of features see: 
https://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/atp-vim/index.php?title=Main_Page 
After looking there you can read the complete documentation in vim (:help atp) 

You can get the latest snaphots (stable/unstable releases) on http://sourceforge.net/projects/atp-vim/ or if you have ATP version 9.2 or higher using :UpdateATP command inside vim (check out :help atp-:UpdateATP)

You can DONATE for this project  (on the project web page: http://sourceforge.net/projects/atp-vim/) 
(see :h atp-donate). 

The project is developed under GPL v3 or higher. 

You can subscribe to the mailing list: 
https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/atp-vim-list 
Its for all kind of purposes: help, bug reports, feature request, comments but also for ANNOUCES (of new releases!) so you can stay up to date. 

Project News: https://sourceforge.net/news/?group_id=513143

This plugin includes: vimscript#3109  (LatexBox by David Munger). 

BUG tracker: send a mail to the mailing list: https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/atp-vim-list 
PROJECT site: http://sourceforge.net/projects/atp-vim/
